BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 1: Puppy-Proofing Your Home) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Puppies explore the world with their mouths and will chew everything in reach.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Get on your hands and knees to see your home from a puppy's eye level.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Secure electrical cords with cord covers or tape them to baseboards.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Move toxic plants, cleaning supplies, and medications to high shelves or locked cabinets.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Pick up small items like coins, buttons, and hair ties that could be swallowed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Block access to stairs and off-limits rooms with baby gates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Remove shoes, socks, and children's toys from the floor during the puppy phase.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Secure trash cans with lids or move them inside cabinets with child locks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Cover or block access to low furniture openings where puppies can get stuck.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Check your yard for toxic plants, gaps in fencing, and pools without barriers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Put away any item you value that the puppy could reach and destroy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Puppy-proofing prevents accidents and protects both your belongings and your puppy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (1) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
