BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 96.96000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 2: The First Night Home) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Bring your puppy home early in the day so they have time to explore before bedtime.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Introduce one room at a time rather than giving access to the entire house.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Take your puppy outside immediately upon arriving home for a bathroom break.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Show them their food and water bowls, crate, and bed location.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Keep the first day calm. Avoid overwhelming the puppy with too many new people.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Children should be gentle and sit on the floor rather than chase the puppy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Place the crate in your bedroom for the first few nights so puppy hears you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Expect crying the first night. Your puppy is away from their mother and siblings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (A warm water bottle wrapped in a towel mimics the warmth of littermates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (A ticking clock or white noise machine can soothe a restless puppy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Take the puppy out for a bathroom break once during the night at first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (The first night is hardest for both of you. It gets better within three to five days.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
