BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 70.08000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 4: Potty Training Step by Step) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Take your puppy outside immediately after waking, eating, drinking, and playing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Choose one designated bathroom spot and take them there every single time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Use a consistent phrase like go potty so they learn what you are asking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Wait patiently outside for up to five minutes. Do not play until they go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Praise enthusiastically and give a small treat the instant they finish.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Take puppies out every 30 to 60 minutes when awake during the early weeks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Watch for signs they need to go: sniffing, circling, squatting, or whining.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (If you catch them starting to go inside, interrupt gently and rush outside.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Never punish accidents after the fact. Puppies cannot connect past actions to punishment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Clean indoor accidents thoroughly with enzyme cleaner to remove all odor.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Regular schedule: out first thing, after meals, after naps, after play, before bed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Most puppies are reliably housetrained between four and six months with consistency.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (4) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
