BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 89.28 600 Td (Chapter 6: Teaching Come and Down) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Come \(recall\) is the most important safety command your dog will ever learn.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Start in a quiet room with minimal distractions. Crouch down and say come happily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (When the puppy runs to you, celebrate like it is the best thing that ever happened.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Never call your puppy to come and then do something unpleasant like crate or bath.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Practice recall during play: call them, reward, then let them go play again.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Use a long training leash in the yard before trusting off-leash recall.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Make yourself more exciting than whatever distracted them. Use high-value treats.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Down means lie all the way down with belly on the floor.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (From a sit, hold a treat at their nose and slowly lower it straight to the ground.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (When they follow the treat down and their elbows touch the floor, reward instantly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Some puppies resist down. Try luring under a low surface like your bent leg.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Practice both commands daily in short two-minute sessions for best retention.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (6) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
