BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 62.400000000000006 600 Td (Chapter 7: Leash Walking Without Pulling) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start leash training indoors where there are fewer distractions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Let your puppy wear the collar and leash around the house to get comfortable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Hold treats at your side and reward the puppy for walking beside you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (When the leash gets tight, stop completely. Do not move forward while pulling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Wait for the puppy to look back at you or create slack, then continue walking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Reward every few steps initially when the leash stays loose.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Change direction frequently to teach the puppy to pay attention to where you go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Use a front-clip harness to reduce pulling power without causing discomfort.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Avoid retractable leashes which teach dogs that pulling creates more freedom.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Practice in low-distraction areas before attempting busy sidewalks or parks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Sniff breaks are important. Let your puppy smell on your terms as a reward.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Loose leash walking takes the most patience of any skill. Expect weeks of practice.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
