BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 116.16 600 Td (Chapter 8: Bite Inhibition) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (All puppies bite and mouth. It is how they explore and play naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Your goal is to teach them that human skin is fragile and biting must be gentle.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (When puppy bites too hard during play, yelp sharply and immediately stop playing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Turn away and ignore the puppy for ten to fifteen seconds after a hard bite.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Resume play after the brief timeout. They will learn that biting ends fun.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Redirect biting to appropriate chew toys whenever their mouth goes to your skin.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Keep a toy in your pocket to substitute whenever they try to mouth your hands.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (If yelping excites them more, simply stand up and walk away calmly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Frozen washcloths soothe teething gums and provide an appropriate chewing outlet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Never slap a puppy's nose or hold their mouth shut as this increases biting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Puppies between three and six months go through intense teething that increases mouthing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (By six months, a properly trained puppy will have a very soft mouth with humans.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
