BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 100.80000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 9: Socialization Guide) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (The critical socialization window is between 3 and 16 weeks of age.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (During this period, expose your puppy to as many positive experiences as possible.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Introduce them to people of all ages, appearances, and body types.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Let them experience different surfaces: grass, gravel, tile, metal, and carpet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Expose them to sounds: vacuum cleaners, thunder recordings, traffic, and doorbells.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Introduce other vaccinated, friendly dogs for appropriate play experiences.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Visit pet-friendly stores, outdoor cafes, and parks for new environments.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Car rides, elevators, automatic doors, and stairs should all become normal.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Always pair new experiences with treats and praise. Never force interactions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (If your puppy shows fear, do not comfort excessively. Calmly redirect and try later.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Puppy socialization classes provide controlled environments for learning.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Under-socialized puppies often become fearful or aggressive adult dogs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (9) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
