BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 13: Common Training Mistakes) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Mistake one: inconsistency. All family members must use the same rules and commands.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Mistake two: training sessions that are too long. Keep them under five minutes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Mistake three: punishing after the fact. Dogs cannot connect delayed consequences.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Mistake four: repeating commands. Say it once. If they do not respond, help them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Mistake five: not rewarding enough. Beginners should treat every correct response.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Mistake six: only training in one location. Practice commands everywhere you go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Mistake seven: expecting too much too fast. Puppies are babies with short attention.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Mistake eight: using their name for punishment. Names should only be positive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Mistake nine: skipping socialization. This window closes and cannot be reopened.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Mistake ten: comparing your puppy to others. Every dog learns at their own pace.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Mistake eleven: stopping training once basics are learned. Training should be lifelong.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Mistakes are normal. What matters is recognizing them and adjusting your approach.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (13) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
