BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 58.56 600 Td (Chapter 14: When to Get Professional Help) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Seek help if your puppy shows aggression toward people or other dogs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Growling, snapping, or biting that breaks skin warrants professional assessment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Extreme fear responses that do not improve with patient gradual exposure.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Severe separation anxiety that causes self-harm or household destruction.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (If you feel frustrated, overwhelmed, or are considering rehoming your puppy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (A good trainer uses positive reinforcement methods without pain or fear.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Avoid any trainer who recommends choke chains, prong collars, or alpha rolls.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Look for certifications like CPDT-KA, KPA, or IAABC membership.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Group puppy classes provide both training guidance and valuable socialization.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Private sessions are better for specific behavioral issues needing focused work.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Ask your veterinarian for trainer recommendations they trust.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Professional help early prevents small issues from becoming serious lifelong problems.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (14) Tj ET

endstream
