BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 43.20000000000002 600 Td (Chapter 15: Training Schedule \(First 8 Weeks\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Week 1: Focus on bonding, crate introduction, and establishing your routine.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Take puppy out every 30 minutes when awake. Praise all outdoor eliminations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Week 2: Begin teaching sit using treat luring. Practice in three short sessions daily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Continue crate training with meals inside and brief door-closed periods.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Week 3: Add the down command and begin name recognition training.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Start leash familiarization indoors. Let them drag a light leash supervised.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Week 4: Introduce stay for one to three seconds after sit. Begin socialization outings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Practice gentle handling: touch paws, ears, mouth daily with treats.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Week 5: Begin recall training in the house. Add gentle leash walking indoors.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Increase alone time gradually. Build from seconds to several minutes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Week 6: Practice all commands in new locations. Extend stay to ten seconds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Weeks 7-8: Combine commands in sequences. Increase distraction levels slowly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (15) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
